  "texts": [
    "Multi-task learning often presents challenges, such as the \"conflicting gradients problem\" [15].",
    "This issue becomes more pronounced in low-rank adaptation due to the limited number of trainable parameters.",
    "Low-Rank Adaptation for MTL ArchitecturesLow-rank decomposition modules are increasingly used to adapt pre-trained models for various tasks [13].",
    "These modules, incorporated into layers that involve matrix multiplication, are notably used in the attention layers of transformerbased models.",
    "The function of these modules can be mathematically described as follows:Output Layeri = W i x + b i + αB i A i x(1)Here, W i and b i are the original weights and biases of the layer."
  ],
